Police found two babies in a fridge at a house in Wesbank last week after receiving a tip-off from the property's owner. CAPE TOWN - A concerned Wesbank ward councillor said that authorities were remaining tight-lipped about the investigation into the killing of two infants in the area. Police found two babies in a fridge at a house in Wesbank last week after receiving a tip-off from the property's owner. Shortly after, a 35-year-old woman was taken in for questioning. Police have not confirmed if the woman was charged or not. Ward councillor Ebrahim Sawant said he had scheduled a meeting with police for an urgent update. "We're trying to get more information but they're not forthcoming. I've requested a meeting as we in leadership in the community need to know what is happening."